3.1 Phillips & Knobe 2009

pk2009 <- ld %>% filter(Study == "Phillips & Knobe, 2009")

######################################## Descriptives All Ratings

# Original Effect
### Neutral + Intentional Violation
pk2009_statsrep <- pk2009 %>% 
  filter(Scenario == "Neutral" | Scenario == "Intentional Violation") %>%
  group_by(QuestionType, Scenario) %>% summarise(mean=mean(response), 
                                   sd=sd(response), 
                                   n=length(response))
pk2009_statsrep %>% 
  print_table()

############################################## DV Rating

############ Original Effect

## We will examine if original effect is replicated

pk2009_reptest <- t.test(pk2009$response[pk2009$Scenario == "Neutral" & pk2009$QuestionType == "Dependent Variable"],
  pk2009$response[pk2009$Scenario == "Intentional Violation" & pk2009$QuestionType == "Dependent Variable"]) 

##Replicated? Yes! 
pander(pk2009_reptest)
Welch Two Sample t-test: pk2009$response[pk2009$Scenario == "Neutral" & pk2009$QuestionType == "Dependent Variable"] and pk2009$response[pk2009$Scenario == "Intentional Violation" & pk2009$QuestionType == "Dependent Variable"] (continued below)
Test statistic df P value Alternative hypothesis mean of x
6.404 161.5 1.577e-09 * * * two.sided 6.082
mean of y
4.534 
pk2009_repEffect <- cohens_d(pk2009$response[pk2009$Scenario == "Neutral" & pk2009$QuestionType == "Dependent Variable"],
                         pk2009$response[pk2009$Scenario == "Intentional Violation" & pk2009$QuestionType == "Dependent Variable"])

##Original Effect Size
print_table(pk2009_repEffect)
Cohens_d CI CI_low CI_high
0.97 0.95 0.65 1.28 
############ New effect

## We will examine if new effect is produced (Ignorance changes effect)
pk2009_newtest <- t.test(pk2009$response[pk2009$Scenario == "Neutral" & pk2009$QuestionType == "Dependent Variable"],

pander(pk2009_newtest)
